01:26:36.831 --> 01:26:47.524
<v Sarah>Mobile team has opportunities for engineers to own end-to-end feature delivery. The dark mode and widget work will have clear ownership.

01:26:47.524 --> 01:26:58.217
<v Sarah>I'm also encouraging cross-platform learning. iOS engineers shadowing Android work and vice versa helps build versatility.

01:26:58.217 --> 01:27:08.910
<v Alex>Frontend team can grow through the component library work. Designing reusable components requires thinking at a higher abstraction level.

01:27:08.910 --> 01:27:19.603
<v Alex>I'm also encouraging engineers to write technical documentation and blog posts. Communication skills are essential for senior roles.

01:27:19.603 --> 01:27:30.297
<v Kim>For design, the AI features provide excellent portfolio pieces. Designers can showcase their ability to tackle novel interaction challenges.

01:27:30.297 --> 01:27:40.990
<v Kim>I'm also mentoring junior designers on research methodology. The AI research sprint will be a learning opportunity for the whole design team.

01:27:40.990 --> 01:27:51.683
<v Mike>For enterprise, the TPM hire will free up time for account executives to focus on strategic relationships rather than operational coordination.

01:27:51.683 --> 01:28:02.376
<v Mike>I'm also creating opportunities for team members to present at internal meetings. Building presentation skills is important for career advancement.

01:28:02.376 --> 01:28:13.069
<v Rachel>These are all great development initiatives. Please ensure career discussions happen in January and that growth plans are documented.

01:28:13.069 --> 01:28:23.762
<v Rachel>We want our people to grow with the company. The investment in their development pays dividends in retention and performance.

01:28:23.762 --> 01:28:34.455
<v Rachel>Alright, I think we've now truly covered everything. Thank you all for the extended discussion. It's been valuable to think through these details.

